'''Romain Ghanem Paul Saïss''' (born 26 March 1990) is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] or a [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]].
Romain Saiss joined Wolves from French Ligue One side [[Angers SCO|Angers]] in August 2016. The midfielder put pen to paper on a four-year deal after joining for an undisclosed fee. Saïss made 35 appearances for Angers in 2015/16, helping the club to a ninth place [[Championnat de France de football|Ligue 1]] finish. Prior to his time with Angers, he had spells with [[Le Havre Athletic Club|Le Havre]], [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]] and [[Olympique de Valence|Valence]]. The midfielder has also featured at international level for [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], including at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia (against [[Iran national football team|Iran]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]]).<ref name="RS18">{{soccerbase season|84821|2017|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>
==Club career== On 3 July 2015, Saïss left [[Le Havre Athletic Club|Le Havre]] and joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[Angers SCO|Angers]] on a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Romain-saiss-signe-deux-ans-a-angers/571491|title=Romain Saïss signe deux ans à Angers [Romain Saïss signs for two years at Angers]|date=3 July 2015|accessdate=23 August 2016|work=L'Equipe|language=French}}</ref>
On 30 August 2016, he moved to England, joining [[Football League Championship|Championship]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for an undisclosed fee on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37221689|title=Romain Saiss: Wolves sign Angers midfielder for undisclosed fee|date=30 August 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 September 2016 in a 2–0 win at Newcastle.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37324949|title=Newcastle 0–2 Wolves|date=17 September 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 30 September 2017 in a 4–0 win against [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41369653|title=Burton Albion 0–4 Wolverhampton Wanderers|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 September 2017}}</ref>
Following Wolves's promotion to the [[Premier League]] in 2018, Saïss made his debut Premier League appearance as a substitute in a 1–1 draw with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Old Trafford]] on 22 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45530717|title=Manchester United 1–1 Wolves: Joao Moutinho earns visitors draw at Old Trafford|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Alex|last=Bysouth|date=22 September 2018|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> Saïss's first start in the Premier League came in a 1–2 defeat away to [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] at the [[Cardiff City Stadium]] on 30 November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38217655|title=Cardiff City 2–1 Wolverhampton Wanderers|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Dafydd |last=Pritchard|date=30 November 2018|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>
Saïss scored his debut Premier League goal for Wolves in a 1–1 draw with [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] at [[Craven Cottage]] on 26 December 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46615162|title=Fulham 1–1 Wolves: Aleksandar Mitrovic 'wants to cry' after missing chances in draw|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Jack|last=Skelton|date=26 December 2018}}</ref> A little over a month later, on 29 January 2019, Saïss scored the opening goal in Wolves's 3–0 home win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] at [[Molineux stadium|Molineux]] to take his goal tally to two in twelve Premier League appearances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46955256|title=Wolves 3-0 West Ham: Jimenez double sees off Hammers|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Steve |last=Sutcliffe|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=84821&season_id=151|title=Games played by Romain Saiss in 2018/2019|publisher=www.soccerbase.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>
On 21 February 2019 it was announced that Saïss had agreed a new contract with Wolves, keeping him at the club until the summer of 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2019/02/21/romain-saiss-signs-new-wolves-deal/|title=Romain Saiss signs new Wolves deal|publisher=[[Express & Star]]|first=Luke|last=Hatfield|date=21 February 2019|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>
==International career== Saïss, who was born and raised in France, chose to represent the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]], for which he qualified through ancestry. He made his debut in a 1–0 friendly loss to [[Togo national football team|Togo]] in November 2012.<ref>http://www.hac-foot.com/actualite/romain-saiss-au-hac-pour-2-ans.html</ref>
In June 2018 he was named in Morocco's 23-man [[Morocco national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia<ref>{{cite web |title=Morocco announce 23-man World Cup squad|url=https://africanfootball.com/news/750416/Morocco-announce-23-man-World-Cup-squad|publisher=African Football|date=4 June 2018|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and featured in Morocco's games in the tournament against [[Iran national football team|Iran]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref name="RS19">{{soccerbase season|84821|2017|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>
